Police have arrested a suspect in connection with the 2016 murder of ANC Youth League official Wandile Ngobeni. The suspect is believed to be the mayor of New Castle Nthuthuko Mahlaba. Reneilwe Serero who is the spokesperson for Police Minister Bheki Cele said she could confirm that a senior official has been arrested although she cannot divulge his name. “I cannot divulge the name of the suspect but he will appear in court within the next 48 hours,” she said. Sowetanlive could not reach the KZN Youth League by the time of publishing. This is a developing story.